OL,3,CMan cleared over masked group's 'show
OL,4,Cof strength'
OL,6,FBoth constables accepted that the man
OL,7,Fthey identified as Mr Matthews was
OL,8,Fmasked with Judge Kerr determining
OL,9,Fthat neither officer "gave any
OL,10,Fevidence of any specific
OL,11,Fcharacteristic which they could rely
OL,12,Fon" to back this up.
OL,14,FBranding this evidence as "general in
OL,15,Fnature", Judge Kerr said: "I'm not
OL,16,Fsure or firmly convinced that he was
OL,17,Fpresent at the scene and I therefore
OL,18,Fmust acquit him of all the charges. I
OL,19,Ffind him not guilty on all three
OL,20,Fcounts."
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/13
