OL,3,CMan cleared over masked group's 'show
OL,4,Cof strength'
OL,6,FRegarding the charges, Judge Kerr
OL,7,Fspoke of the unlawful assembly offence
OL,8,Fand said this constituted an
OL,9,Fallegation that Lammey assembled with
OL,10,Fothers with intent to encourage the
OL,11,Fcommission of a crime by open force.
OL,13,FThe judge said that after considering
OL,14,Fall the evidence, which included
OL,15,Ffootage from police body-worn cameras,
OL,16,Fhe was "not satisfied" it had been
OL,17,Festablished that open force was
OL,18,Fdisplayed or that the intent was to
OL,19,Fcommit a crime by open force.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/13
